    rationale: "The Finkelstein test stretches the first dorsal compartment tendons \u2014 the abductor pollicis longus (APL) and extensor pollicis brevis (EPB) \u2014 as they pass through their shared tendon sheath at the radial styloid. Tucking the thumb inside the fist and ulnar-deviating the wrist maximally elongates these tendons, reproducing pain in De Quervain tenosynovitis. The extensor carpi radialis tendons (A) are in the second dorsal compartment. The flexor pollicis longus (C) is a volar structure. The extensor pollicis longus (D) is in the third dorsal compartment.",
