    rationale: "Erythema overlying a joint is an urgent clinical signal that mandates immediate exclusion of septic arthritis. Bacterial infection within a joint space can destroy articular cartilage within hours due to proteolytic enzymes released by bacteria and neutrophils. This is a medical emergency requiring urgent joint aspiration and culture. While gout, pseudogout, and RA can also cause erythema, septic arthritis must be ruled out first because the consequences of delayed treatment are irreversible joint destruction and systemic sepsis.",
