    rationale: "A T-score of \u22121.8 falls between \u22121.0 and \u22122.5, which defines osteopenia. This is not normal bone density, but it does not yet meet the threshold for osteoporosis (\u2264 \u22122.5). Management includes calcium and vitamin D supplementation, weight-bearing exercise, fall prevention, and addressing modifiable risk factors. Bisphosphonates are reserved for osteoporosis (T-score \u2264 \u22122.5) or osteopenia with high fracture risk (e.g., prior fragility fracture). Repeat DEXA is typically recommended in 1\u20132 years for osteopenia, not 10 years.",
