    rationale: "Ankylosing spondylitis is a seronegative spondyloarthropathy that primarily involves the spine and sacroiliac joints. The morning stiffness pattern reflects inflammatory pathophysiology: during rest, inflammatory mediators (TNF-\u03b1, IL-17) accumulate in affected joints, causing stiffness. Physical activity promotes synovial fluid circulation and reduces local cytokine concentration, explaining why stiffness improves with exercise \u2014 the opposite of osteoarthritis. Disc hydration explains some morning stiffness in mechanical pain but not the >1 hour duration or exercise improvement seen in AS.",
