    rationale: "Uric acid solubility decreases at lower temperatures. The first MTP joint, being a distal peripheral joint, has a lower local temperature than central joints. Combined with the relatively higher urate concentration in peripheral tissues, this creates ideal conditions for monosodium urate crystal nucleation and deposition. This is the primary physiological explanation for podagra. Synovial membrane permeability, chondrocyte urate transporters, and microtrauma are not the established mechanisms for this predilection.",
