    rationale: "Precise goniometric documentation (e.g., 45\u00b0\u2192120\u00b0 rather than 'limited flexion') provides an objective, reproducible measurement that allows clinicians to track disease progression, monitor treatment response, and compare findings across visits and providers. It also creates legally defensible records in cases of disability determination, workers' compensation, or litigation. Vague descriptors like 'limited ROM' are subjective and cannot be reliably compared over time. Goniometry does not replace imaging and is not limited to surgical candidates.",
